@mangoo:
There's actually an easier way to do that.
If you Ctrl-click on the diamond rather than a normal click when you mark an item available, it marks it with a bluish-purple diamond instead of a green one, which means only that specific gemming of that item is available.

The optimizer still seems to ignore template socket colors in 2.3.16 as it keeps putting red gems into blue sockets though there's no template for that.

@midnightlynx: thanks, I wasn't aware of this and it helped. But I still think that a custom template would be the better way to do so, e.g. I don't have to regem new items manually or if I respec (as a mage from arcane to fire) and value
crit gems higher than haste then I only have to change one template and not all of my items in rawr.
